=\"#feedbackModal_main_5830903\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Jan 19, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104ryk1705565545612.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/ryk1705565545612.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/ryk1705565545612.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"zit1665702685863\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n                             \n Create and Maintain Global Objects \n      \n   </h1>\n<div class=\"body taskbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Create global objects such as global ProcScripts and messages in a runtime library.\n </p>\n<section><ol class=\"ol steps\"><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"zit1665702685863__li_d6011e1_d6012e1_d6013e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">In the Uniface IDE, choose <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">More Editors</span> and select the type of global object (under the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Library</span> heading.)\n </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"zit1665702685863__li_d6014e1_d6015e1_d6016e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">In the Open Library dialog, create or select the library to hold the objects. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ita1705565048634.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ita1705565048634.html\" title=\"To create libraries of modeled properties, global objects, and language setups, use the editors available in the More Editors menu.\">Create a Library for Modeled Properties or Global Objects</a>.\n                              </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"zit1665702685863__li_d6017e1_d6018e1_d6019e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">To create a new object, click <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">New</span>.\n </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"zit1665702685863__li_d6020e1_d6021e1_d6022e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">To update an existing object, select it in the object list.\n </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"zit1665702685863__li_d6023e1_d6024e1_d6025e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Set the object properties as required.\n </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<div class=\"note tip note_tip\" id=\"zit1665702685863__note_w3773ab1b5b1b9b3b1_w3774ab1b5b1b9b3_w3775ab1b5b1b9_w3776ab1b5b1_w3777ab1b5_w3778ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">Tip:</span> Press F1 to display help about the properties of object.</div>\n</div>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"zit1665702685863__li_d6026e1_d6027e1_d6028e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">If the object requires compilation, click the compile icon (if available) or choose <span class=\"ph menucascade\"><span class=\"ph uicontrol\">File&gt;Compile</span></span> .\n </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"zit1665702685863__li_d6029e1_d6030e1_d6031e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"zit1665702685863__p_d12758e1_d12759e1_d12760e1\">To save the object, choose <span class=\"ph menucascade\"><span class=\"ph uicontrol\">File</span><abbr title=\"and then\"> &gt; </abbr><span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Save</span></span>. </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">Alternatively, click <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">OK</span>to (compile and) save the object,\n               and close the editor.</div>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"zit1665702685863__li_d6032e1_d6033e1_d6034e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">To delete an object, select it and click <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Delete</span> (if\n               available) or choose <span class=\"ph menucascade\"><span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Edit</span><abbr title=\"and then\"> &gt; </abbr><span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Delete <var class=\"keyword varname\">&lt;Object&gt;</var></span></span>. </span>\n</li></ol></section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/loi1665702847852.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Global Objects</a><p>A global object is a reusable, technology-independent object that is centrally stored and available to all components running on a given host, regardless of the deployment environment.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_5830903\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_5830903\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Create and Maintain Global Objects Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Jan 19, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Create and Maintain Global Objects Create global objects such as global ProcScripts and messages in a runtime library. In the Uniface IDE, choose More Editors and select the type of global object (under the Library heading.) In the Open Library dialog, create or select the library to hold the objects. For more information, see Create a Library for Modeled Properties or Global Objects . To create a new object, click New . To update an existing object, select it in the object list. Set the object properties as required. Tip: Press F1 to display help about the properties of object. If the object requires compilation, click the compile icon (if available) or choose File>Compile . To save the object, choose File > Save . Alternatively, click OK to (compile and) save the object, and close the editor. To delete an object, select it and click Delete (if available) or choose Edit > Delete <Object> . Related Links Global Objects A global object is a reusable, technology-independent object that is centrally stored and available to all components running on a given host, regardless of the deployment environment. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}